description: From Spanish javalina, jabalina, feminine form of jabalí (“wild boar”), from Andalusian Arabic جَبَلِي‎ (jabalī) (in خِنْزِير جَبَلِيّ‎ (ḵinzīr jabaliyy, “mountain pig”)), from Arabic جَبَل‎ (jabal, “mountain”). Cognate with Portuguese javalina, and similar in other Iberian languages.

entries.meaning: (Canada, US) The peccary, especially the collared peccary. [from 19th c.]
